🧑‍💻 Jenkins Freestyle CI Checks - Assignment 03

This project demonstrates Continuous Integration (CI) checks on multiple repositories using Jenkins Freestyle Jobs, including report generation, artifact management, and automated failure notifications.

📌 Overview

The goal of this assignment is to:

Perform CI checks on three repositories (Python, GoLang, Java)
Configure Jenkins Freestyle Jobs for each repo
Implement Generic & Advanced CI Checks such as:
Unit Testing
Code Coverage
Dependency Analysis
Credential Scanning
Store reports in Jenkins
Manage build artifacts locally or remotely
Configure notifications via Email, Slack, or Telegram on failures
⚙️ Tools & Technologies
Jenkins Freestyle Jobs
GitHub Repositories
Python / GoLang / Java Build Tools
Jenkins Plugins:
JUnit / xUnit
Cobertura / JaCoCo (Code Coverage)
Artifact Management
Slack / Email Notification Plugins
Linux (Ubuntu/CentOS)
Slack / Email / Telegram for notifications
🚀 Target Repositories
Language	Repository URL
Python	https://github.com/OT-MICROSERVICES/attendance-api
GoLang	https://github.com/OT-MICROSERVICES/employee-api
Java	https://github.com/opstree/spring3hibernate.git
🛠️ Jenkins Freestyle Jobs Setup
1️⃣ Python Repository Job
Configuration
Job Type: Freestyle Project
Source Code Management: Git → Python repo
Build Steps:
Install dependencies (pip install -r requirements.txt)
Run Unit Tests (pytest --junitxml=report.xml)
Run Static Analysis / Linting (flake8 .)
Credential / Security Scanning (e.g., bandit -r .)
Reports & Artifacts
Store report.xml as JUnit report
Save logs or test reports as artifacts
